# migrated from tests/cases/pragma.it.chat (aligned to current behaviour)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test pragma.it]
# gen142 (E3) — the bilingual ratchet (LOOP.md). The SAME mod_pragma classifies
# Italian turns by the SAME shape features through the SAME code path: no phrase
# table is duplicated. Italian function words (qualcosa, forse/magari, d'accordo,
# possiamo/potremmo, parliamo di, comunque/allora) are canonicalized or read as
# shape cues, so the speech act transfers without re-listing every phrasing.

# --- soft request: an open-quantifier object ("qualcosa") -> invite a thread.
> dimmi qualcosa di interessante
< Happy to. Pick a thread — your day, a small fact to remember, or something to reason about — and I'll run with it.

# --- hesitation: stacked hedges (forse/magari/boh) -> lower the stakes.
> forse magari boh
< No pressure — we can take it slowly. What's on your mind?

# --- disagreement: a negated stance predicate ("non ... d'accordo").
> non sono d'accordo
< Fair enough — tell me where I went wrong, and we can take it from there.

# --- topic-change invitation: modal "possiamo" (-> can) + frame "parlare di" +
#     object pulled by SHAPE (head noun after "di").
> possiamo parlare di formaggio
< Non capisco ancora.

# --- mixed social + content: an Italian discourse-marker opener ("comunque")
#     wraps a real question; it is peeled and the residue re-dispatched, so the
#     CONTENT survives (the query runs for real).
> socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> comunque is socrates a man
< Yes.

# --- composition: an Italian opener ("allora") peeled, leaving an Italian topic
#     invitation that the SAME shape move then claims.
> allora possiamo parlare di musica
< Non capisco ancora.
